cs.CL, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE 

This paper proposes a new decoding algorithm for neural sequence models and demonstrates its effectiveness on tasks such as image captioning, machine translation, and visual question generation. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). However, since the paper also deals with image-related tasks, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is also a likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the exploration and exploitation of the search space, which suggests a connection to reinforcement learning and optimization, making cs.LG (Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely sub-categories as well. Finally, since the paper proposes a new algorithm, it may also be relevant to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
